  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>We present XTT, a version of Cartesian cubical type theory specialized for Bishop sets à la <fr:link href="thierrycoquand.xml" title="Thierry Coquand" addr="thierrycoquand" type="local">Coquand</fr:link>, in which every type enjoys a definitional version of the uniqueness of identity proofs. Using cubical notions, XTT reconstructs many of the ideas underlying Observational Type Theory, a version of intensional type theory that supports function extensionality. We prove the canonicity property of XTT (that every closed boolean is definitionally equal to a constant) by Artin gluing.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
